In-Reply-To: <CAKWaqjYzSy+4ATH0KGiSQHn9S2q8UrxJq7PvLGF9sy==4cRLPg@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAKWaqja1AuzVwL5pPits3gqbF7bMW0VJrw8GftVSC=fZDu5EbA@mail.gmail.com>
 <2eab4ae2920e4cd281ae15555365ea6c@UM-MAIL3214.unimaas.nl>
 <CAKWaqjYzSy+4ATH0KGiSQHn9S2q8UrxJq7PvLGF9sy==4cRLPg@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <35a06957c1fd418e8af071cdfe3e4716@UM-MAIL3214.unimaas.nl>

It's just the multivariate version of Cochrane's Q-test. It does not estimate a random-effects model. It simply tests whether the observed amount of variability is larger than expected based on the sampling variances (and their covariances when V includes those) and any moderators specified.

Best,
Wolfgang

